result.execSummary:
The defendant Bryan James Strain was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Prisoner Throw/Expel Bodily Substances [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.43(2m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 1:36 PM Defendant Bryan James Strain appeared by video, in custody at Jackson Correctional.  Attorney Melissa Anne Frost appeared by video for Bryan James Strain.  Prosecuting attorney Gerald Anthony Urbik in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant waives right to appear in person in courtroom. Defendant pleads guilty to Count 1; Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed and read in.  Defendant waives right to pre sentence investigation. Court orders sentence withheld, 3 years probation, consecutive to any other sentence currently serving, any treatment deemed necessary, maintain absolute sobriety, no alcohol, may not possess or consume any controlled substances unless prescribed by a medical professional, may not enter any bars, taverns or establishments where the primary source of revenue is the sale of alcohol, costs due to Clerk of Court, 0 days sentence credit.
